id: pm-9g87
title: pm next hides completed-container closeout rows while leaf work exists
description: "Follow-up to pm-2n6i: pm next now ranks concrete ready leaf work ahead of 100%-complete open containers, but the default ready queue still emits completed-container closeout rows while actionable leaf work exists. Hide those governance closeout rows from the ready queue until there is no concrete leaf work, so agent loops stay token-focused on implementation work while still surfacing closeout when it becomes the next action."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,"area:cli",context-management
created_at: "2026-06-27T20:44:06.865Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-27T20:59:32.758Z"
author: codex-implementation
parent: pm-mpbb
resolution: "Resolved by projecting ranked ready rows through a concrete-leaf filter: completed-container closeout candidates remain available, but are hidden from the normal ready queue until no concrete leaf work is ready."
expected_result: Agent-facing pm next output should stay focused on concrete leaf work while still surfacing completed-container governance closeout when it becomes the next action.
actual_result: "pm next now recommends and lists concrete leaf work first, omits completed-container closeout rows while leaf work exists, and shows the closeout row with rationale once leaf work is closed."
